{"lemma":"حِكْمَة","slug":"حِكْمَة","root":"ح.ك.م","root_slug":"ح-ك-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ك-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حِكْمَة","root":"حكم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":20},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8708","n8709","n8716","n8717"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%83%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wisdom","examples":[{"text":"اُدْعُ إِلَىٰ سَبِيلِ رَبِّكَ بِٱلْحِكْمَةِ وَٱلْمَوْعِظَةِ ٱلْحَسَنَةِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knowledge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"medical art","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"philosophy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"justice, equity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reason"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"secret decree of God"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prophecy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the Qur'an"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the Gospel","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bridle, bit","examples":[{"text":"القَائِدَ الْخَيْلَ مَنْكُوبًا دَوَابِرُهَا قَدِّ أُحْكِمَتْ حَكَمَاتِ الْقِدِّ والأبَقا","english":"Leader of a horse of veering hind legs, fastened by bridles of leather strips and banana fibres."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, rank, station, position"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the verbal noun of حَكُمَ (ḥakuma, “to be wise”). Compare Hebrew חָכְמָה (ḥokhmá, “wisdom”) and Ugaritic 𐎈𐎋𐎎𐎚 (ḥkmt)."},"ipa":["/ħik.ma/","/ħa.ka.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8708","headword_ar":"حَكَمَهُ","root":"Hkm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, [in the TK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakomN","text_ar":"حَكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) in its primary acceptation, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prevented, restrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld, him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from acting in an evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a corrupt, manner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmhu","text_ar":"احكمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from doing that which he desired;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmhu","text_ar":"احكمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hk~mhu","text_ar":"حكّمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHokiymN","text_ar":"تَحْكِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukuwmapN","text_ar":"حُكُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is another inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakamahu","text_ar":"حَكَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and], accord. to As, primarily signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back from wrongdoing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Ibrá- heem En-Nakha'ee is related to have said, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~imi","text_ar":"حَكِّمِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyatiyma kamaA tuHak~imu waladaka","text_ar":"اليَتِيمَ كَمَا تُحَكِّمُ وَلَدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Restrain thou the orphan from acting in an evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a corrupt, manner, and make him good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"virtuous, as thou restrainest thine offspring"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and of every one whom thou preventest, or restrainest, or withholdest, from doing a thing, thou sayest, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakamotuhu","text_ar":"حَكَمْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hk~mth","text_ar":"حكّمته","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmth","text_ar":"احكمته","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to Aboo-Sa'eed Ed-Dareer, as related by Sh, the forementioned saying of En-Nakh'ee means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let the orphan decide respecting his property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"when he is good, or virtuous,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as thou lettest thine offspring"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; but this explanation is not approved. (Az, TA.) And Jereer says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"sufahaA='akumo ↓ \n      A^FbaniY Haniyfapa A^aHokimuwA\n                      \n                     \n                        A_in~iY A^axaAfu Ealayokumu A^ano A^agoDabaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O sons of Haneefeh, restrain your lightwitted ones: verily I fear for you that I may be angry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) i. e., restrain and prevent them from opposing me. (TA.) You say, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani","text_ar":"عَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmhu","text_ar":"احكمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to turn back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revert, from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama Alfarasa","text_ar":"حَكَمَ الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmhu","text_ar":"احكمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hk~mhu","text_ar":"حكّمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pulled in the horse by the bridle and bit, to stop him; he curbed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restrained, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama Ald~aAb~apa","text_ar":"حَكَمَ الدَّابَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasa","text_ar":"الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakomN","text_ar":"حَكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S; [so in my two copies of that work;]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHokamahaA","text_ar":"اَحْكَمَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmhu","text_ar":"احكمهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakamap","text_ar":"حَكَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the bit of the beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K.) ―         -b3-  And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hk~m","text_ar":"حكّم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHawaAdiva","text_ar":"الحَوَادِثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He controlled events:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHak~amN","text_ar":"مُحَكَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (MF.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakamotu Ealayohi bika*aA","text_ar":"حَكَمْتُ عَلَيْهِ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I prevented, restrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld, him from doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffering, any other than such a thing, so that he could not escape it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [Hence it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I condemned him to such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, the payment of a fine or of a debt, and death.] And hence, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama","text_ar":"حَكَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukuwmapN","text_ar":"حُكُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He judged, gave judgment, passed sentence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decided judicially,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his favour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama Ealayohi biAlA^amori","text_ar":"حَكَمَ عَلَيْهِ بِالاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He decided judicially the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama lahu Ealayohi bika*aA","text_ar":"حَكَمَ لَهُ عَلَيْهِ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He awarded by judicial sentence in his favour, against him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. another person),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama Ealayohi","text_ar":"حَكَمَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exercised judicial authority, jurisdiction, rule, dominion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"government, over him."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama bika*aA","text_ar":"حَكَمَ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ordered, ordained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decreed, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama Eani AlA^amori","text_ar":"حَكَمَ عَنِ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverted, from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Az, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakuma","text_ar":"حَكُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, TA,) with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karuma","text_ar":"كَرُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakama","text_ar":"حَكَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Lexicons of Golius and Freytag,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL, MA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikomapN","text_ar":"حِكْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakiymN","text_ar":"حَكِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wise, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, KL, MA, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hkm","text_ar":"حكم"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hkm","text_ar":"حكم"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the TA, without any syll. signs, app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakuma","text_ar":"حَكُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] is said of a man, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reached the utmost point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"degree, in its meaning"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonaAhu","text_ar":"مَعْنَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in what is the radical meaning of the verb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in judging;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDuwa","text_ar":"قَضُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]); in praising, not in dispraising. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA","Mgh","MA","KL"]},{"entry_id":"n8709","headword_ar":"حكّمهُ","root":"Hkm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHokiymN","text_ar":"تَحْكِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in five places. ―         -b2-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him judge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he committed to him the office of judging, giving judgment, passing sentence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deciding judicially;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ordered him to judge, give judgment, pass sentence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decide judicially;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he allowed him to judge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~amotuhu fiY maAliY","text_ar":"حَكَّمْتُهُ فِى مَالِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him authority to judge, give judgment, pass sentence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decide judicially, respecting my property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~amati AlxawaAriju","text_ar":"حَكَّمَتِ الخَوَارِجُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"schismatics called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xwArj","text_ar":"خوارج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asserted that judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHukomu","text_ar":"الحُكْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belongs not to any but God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHokiymu AlHaruwriy~api","text_ar":"تَحْكِيمُ الحَرُورِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the K, erroneously, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHak~umu","text_ar":"تَحَكُّمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHrwry~p","text_ar":"الحروريّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The assertion of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"schismatics called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hrwry~p","text_ar":"حروريّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that there is no judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hukom","text_ar":"حُكْم"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but God's,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that there is no judge"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakam","text_ar":"حَكَم"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n8716","headword_ar":"حِكْمَةٌ","root":"Hkm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[properly, or primarily,] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What prevents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restrains, from ignorant behaviour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [in its most usual sense, which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wisdom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with explanations here following,] it is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakamapN","text_ar":"حَكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying a certain appertenance of a beast, [a kind of curb,] because it prevents its possessor from having bad dispositions: (Msb:) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) or [generally]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the true natures of things, and action according to the requirements thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore it is divided into intellectual and practical: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, of the intellectual faculty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the theological"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hikomap","text_ar":"حِكْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the Kur xxxi. 11, by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hikomap","text_ar":"حِكْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"given by God to Lukmán, is meant the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence of the intellect in accordance with the statutes of the law:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) in the conventional language of the learned, it means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfecting of the human mind by the acquisition of the speculative sciences, and of the complete faculty of doing excellent deeds, according to the ability possessed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd on the passage of the Kur above mentioned:) or it means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attainment of that which is true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right, by knowledge and by deed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that in God it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of things, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origination thereof in the most perfect manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, in man, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge and doing of good things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquaintance with the most excellent of things by the most excellent kind of knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and in the modern language,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"philosophy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikamN","text_ar":"حِكَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Equity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"justice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judicial decision;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukomN","text_ar":"حُكْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilomN","text_ar":"حِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Forbearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clemency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"management of one's soul and temper on the occasion of excitement of anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"which, if correct, is nearly the same as equity or justice. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Obedience of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge in matters of religion, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting agreeably therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverential fear; piety; pious fear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstinence from unlawful things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying, that which is right:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reflection upon what God has commanded, and doing according thereto."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowledge of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the interpretation of the Kur-án, and saying that which is right in relation to it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur ii. 272. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gift of prophecy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prophetic office;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apostleship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur ii. 252 and iii. 43 and xxxviii. 19: (TA:) or in the [first and] last of these instances it means ―         -b7-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Book of the Psalms"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of David]: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, agreeable with the truth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and it also means [in other instances] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Book of the Law of Moses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gospel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Kur-án:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) because each of these comprises what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHikomapu AlmanoTuwqu bihaA","text_ar":"الحِكْمَةُ المَنْطُوقُ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the secrets of the sciences of the law and of the course of conduct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHikomapu Almasokuwtu EanohaA","text_ar":"الحِكْمَةُ المَسْكُوتُ عَنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the secrets of the science of the Divine Essence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","S","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n8717","headword_ar":"حَكَمَةٌ","root":"Hkm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of curb for a horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain appertenance of a beast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because it renders him manageable, or submissive, to the rider, and prevents him from being refractory and the like; (Msb;) or because it prevents him from vehement running: (TA:) it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lijaAm","text_ar":"لِجَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or bridle]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that surrounds the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hanak","text_ar":"حَنَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part beneath the chin and lower jaw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the Arabs used to make it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of untanned thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hemp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because what they aimed at was courage, not finery: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ljAm","text_ar":"لجام"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that surrounds the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanakaAni","text_ar":"حَنَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which word app. here means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two jaws"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the horse, and in which are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attached"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAraAni","text_ar":"عِذَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two side-pieces of the headstall, that lie against the two cheeks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ring which surrounds"},{"kind":"page_break","n":618},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marosin","text_ar":"مَرْسِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the nose which is the place of the halter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hanak","text_ar":"حَنَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part beneath the chin and lower jaw"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd in his Book on the Saddle and Bridle:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ring which is upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mouth of the horse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakamaAtN","text_ar":"حَكَمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HakamN","text_ar":"حَكَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Zuheyr says, describing horses,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"HakamaAti Alqid~i wa AlA^abaqaA ↓ \n      qado A^uHokimato"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado A^uHokimato biHakamaAti Alqid~i wa biHakamaAti AlA^abaqi","text_ar":"قَدْ اُحْكِمَتْ بِحَكَمَاتِ القِدِّ وَ بِحَكَمَاتِ الاَبَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That had been curbed with curbs of untanned thong, and with curbs of hemp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) or, accord. to Abu-l-Hasan, [the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that had been furnished with curbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; for he says that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHkmt","text_ar":"احكمت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here made trans. because it implies the signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qul~idato","text_ar":"قُلِّدَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) some relate the hemistich thus:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"HakamaAti Alqid~i wa AlA^abaqaA ↓ \n      maHokuwmapF"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furnished with curbs of untanned thong, and hemp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sheep (S, K) or goat. (S.) ―         -b3-  And, of a man, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower part of the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a metaphorical term from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakamap","text_ar":"حَكَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lijaAm","text_ar":"لِجَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or [in some copies of the K “ and ”] (tropical:)  his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to the CK, or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man:] and (tropical:)  his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaEa A@ll~`hu Hakamatahu","text_ar":"رَفَعَ ا@للّٰهُ حَكَمَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God exalted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God exalt, his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the stooping of the head is a characteristic of the low, or abject. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EinodanaA HakamapN","text_ar":"لَهُ عِنْدَنَا حَكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has rank in our estimation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAliY AlHakamapi","text_ar":"عَالِى الحَكَمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is elevated in respect of rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.)       -A2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAkimN","text_ar":"حَاكِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is a pl.]"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","ISh"]}]}}